# Subdomain Map PagerDuty

One-shot Python tool that maps your PagerDuty topology and incident volume into:
- An XLSX workbook (Services, EscalationPolicies, Teams, Schedules, BusinessServices, Edges)
- Visuals:
  - Graphviz DOT (+ PNG if Graphviz is installed)
  - Mermaid Markdown
  - Self-contained interactive HTML (open locally)

## Quick start

1) Set your PagerDuty API token (read-only recommended):
```bash
export PD_API_TOKEN="<​your_token>"
Create a virtual environment and install dependencies:
bash
Copy
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -r requirements.txt
Optional: PNG rendering for DOT
bash
Copy
brew install graphviz
Run (US region by default):
bash
Copy
python pd_topology_map.py --volume-window last_30d --output xlsx --visual all --basename pd_topology_map --overwrite --include-business-services
Outputs:

pd_topology_map.xlsx
pd_topology_map.dot and pd_topology_map.png (PNG only if Graphviz installed)
pd_topology_map.mermaid.md
pd_topology_map.html
Options
--api-host:
US: https://api.pagerduty.com (default)
EU: https://api.eu.pagerduty.com
--volume-window: last_7d | last_30d | last_90d | custom
For custom, provide --start-iso and --end-iso (UTC, ends with Z)
--include-business-services: attempts to fetch Business Services + Dependencies (best-effort)
--include-users: include Users and OnCall (off by default)
--visual: all | dot | mermaid | html
--basename: base filename for outputs
--overwrite: overwrite existing output files
Security
No secrets are stored in the repo.
Set PD_API_TOKEN via environment variable. Rotate if exposed.
License
See LICENSE.md


FAQ.md
```markdown
# FAQ

## I get `command not found: python`
Use `python3` or activate your virtual environment:
```bash
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
python --version
ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'openpyxl'
Install Python packages with pip (not Homebrew):

bash
Copy
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
DOT PNG not generated
PNG requires Graphviz:

bash
Copy
brew install graphviz
401 Unauthorized
Ensure the token is set in the current shell:

bash
Copy
export PD_API_TOKEN="<​your_token>"
EU region
bash
Copy
python pd_topology_map.py --api-host https://api.eu.pagerduty.com ...
Business services/dependencies missing
Might not be enabled in your account. Script logs a warning and continues.

Rate limited (429)
Script retries with backoff. If persistent, slow down or split runs.

Large orgs
For <100 services it should be quick. Parallelization can be added later if needed.

Where are outputs written?
Current directory. Use --basename and --overwrite to control filenames.


